news.title: Coimbatore corporation demolishes 13 houses on Kannapiran Mills Road
news.para: A stretch of nearly 200 metres of the 40 feet road had been encroached on by 30 families for almost 25 years. The encroachment shrunk the road to a nearly 25 feet road in this stretch.

news.title: Maharashtra government to exclude height of stilt parking from buildings under 12.5% scheme
news.para: Deputy CM Eknath Shinde told the legislative council that the redevelopment of many 12.5 per cent scheme plots was stuck as the current development regulations do not include a clause excluding the height of stilt parking.

news.title: Kanpur civic body  takes action against shopkeepers for over Rs 10.17 lakh rent dues
news.para: ​​According to zonal officer of Vidya Sagar Zone-1, multiple notices were issued to defaulting shopkeepers, who failed to settle their rent and arrears.

news.title: Land measuring 31,455 acres illegally occupied in 507 panchayats in Punjab: Report
news.para: An audit of the ULBs revealed that user charges of Rs 510.56 crore on account of water supply and sewerage charges, house tax, property tax, rent from shops, and mobile tower charges were pending for recovery.

news.title: ED investigates Vasai illegal buildings case, summons POA holder
news.para: The ED is looking into the entire cycle of events on how the land was grabbed and how illegal buildings were constructed over the years in Agarwal Nagri, Vasai east.

news.title: Criminal offences against those taking up illegal land plotting in Pune: Revenue minister
news.para: A committee with police officers, forest department officers, and other authorities will be formed to avoid illegal constructions in these areas.

news.title: Property registration offices in Pune to remain open from March 29 to 31
news.para: The registration department issued a circular in this regard on Tuesday taking into account Gudi Padwa, Id and the last day of this fiscal on Monday next week.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh minister directs collectors to remove private lands from 22A register
news.para: The chief minister wants all land-related issues to be resolved at the field level itself. We have initiated several reforms in the revenue dept to resolve the issues," the minister added.

news.title: Primus plans to invest Rs 1,500 crore to expand its multi-generational community
news.para: Primus Senior Living plans to invest around Rs 470 crore in the next few quarters to launch about three projects. It also plans to cross Rs 380 crore revenue by the financial year 2025-26.

news.title: China: Beijing Capital seeks to raise upto $500 million in dollar bond
news.para: Greentown China in February sold $350 million worth of three-year dollar bonds in the first Chinese property developer dollar bond transaction in two years.

news.title: Adani Group keen to acquire Jaiprakash Associates by insolvency: Sources
news.para: Earlier this month, the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) directed that the resolution plans to acquire JAL through the insolvency process should be invited for the entire company as a going concern and not by dividing its different business verticals.

news.title: Builders turn to 3D printing and factory-built homes to address housing crisis in US
news.para: It's a response to the country's shortfall of millions of homes that has led to skyrocketing prices, plunging millions into poverty.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body names 100 biggest property tax defaulters
news.para: In such a situation, the UMC decided to take action against these individuals. As a first step, they put up a list of the 100 biggest property tax defaulters in the city.

news.title: New home sales rise 1.8% in USA in February 2025
news.para: New home sales increased 1.8% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 676,000 units last month, the Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Tuesday.

news.title: After HC order, panchayats in Goa to act against illegal constructions
news.para: In its detailed March 6 order, the high court issued several directions to authorities as they go about removing illegal constructions and put measures in place.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government creates 125 new towns in eight years
news.para: Principal secretary of the department, Amrit Abhijat said that presently 21 schemes to strengthen urban services, infrastructure and social sectors are being run.

news.title: BDA approves building plans for 158 high-rises in Bhubaneswar despite BMC's authority
news.para: Responding to a query by legislator Upasana Mohapatra, the minister stated that as per information received from BDA, it accorded building plan approvals to 158 high-rises and received sanction fees of Rs 48.30 crore in the past five years.

news.title: Indore: IDA may propose Rs 1,650 crore budget for  new residential schemes
news.para: There is also a plan to initiate the construction of a convention centre with a capacity of around 10,000 on approximately 17 hectares of land near the Super Corridor. Besides, the IDA is contemplating developing two new ISBTs on Bhopal and Dhar Road.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 1,850 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body issued 3,928 notices to residential property owners who had not cleared their property tax dues. AMC officials cautioned that failure to pay would result in disconnection of water and sewerage services.

news.title: BirlaNu plans to invest $150 million by 2028
news.para: "We’ve doubled our AAC block capacity in Chennai to four lakh cubic meters per year and are marking our expansion into the home and interiors space, said Akshat Seth, managing director and CEO of BirlaNu.
